name: nanonet
overview:
nanonet is the faster way to browse the internet. With a simple theory, nanonet has managed to create one of the fastest internet browsers in the world. This theory is that without unnecessary ad-ons (RSS feeds, bookmarks, favorites, calendars, printable pages etc…), the browser would run a lot faster.

Created in January, 2009, nanonet launched to the world in February. It costs Â£3 to download nanonet. To download it, you must visit www.thenanonet.com and follow the steps. Pay using PayPal and then click on the link that will bring you to the download page where you can download nanonet directly from there.

Then main font in nanonet is “Levenim” size 9. The only features included in nanonet are a forward button, a back button, a home button and an address bar. All the fat is scraped away and nanonet is slimed down so that it is 100% pure internet.

nanonet is proven to be upto 2.5 times faster than Internet Explorer, upto 2 times faster than Mozilla Firefox and upto 1.7 times faster than Apple’s Safari.
